# reprovision config — OPTIONAL.
#
# You normally do NOT need this file. The secret *references* (op:// pointers into the
# team "RelOps" 1Password vault) are baked into the config defaults, so a fresh checkout
# just needs `op signin`. Copy this to `.env` only to OVERRIDE a default — e.g. a different
# vault/item, or to use GCP Secret Manager instead of 1Password.
#
# Secrets are resolved at run time (see the README "Secrets" section). References are not
# secrets; never put an actual secret in here.

# --- Defaults (shown for reference; uncomment to override) ---

# REPROVISION_SSH_ADMIN_PASSWORD_REF="op://RelOps/DEP Provisioned Mac Admin Account SimpleMDM SSH/password"
# REPROVISION_SIMPLEMDM_API_KEY_REF="op://RelOps/SimpleMDM API admin/password"
# REPROVISION_TC_CLIENT_ID_REF="op://RelOps/Taskcluster Quarantine/username"
# REPROVISION_TC_ACCESS_TOKEN_REF="op://RelOps/Taskcluster Quarantine/password"

# Admin SSH private key (the counterpart to what relops_key_admin installs on the workers).
# Set this to drive admin@ without a local key — point at an op:// SSH-key ref. Empty (the
# default) makes ssh fall back to your agent / ~/.ssh identities.
# REPROVISION_SSH_ADMIN_KEY_REF="op://RelOps/<admin ssh key item>/private key"

# To use GCP Secret Manager for a secret instead, set its _REF to a secret id and
# authenticate with `gcloud auth login`:
# REPROVISION_GCP_PROJECT=relops-bootstrap
# REPROVISION_SIMPLEMDM_API_KEY_REF=simplemdm-api-token

# Direct-value overrides (CI / debugging only — keeps secrets out of the shell otherwise):
# REPROVISION_SSH_ADMIN_PASSWORD=...
# REPROVISION_SIMPLEMDM_API_KEY=...
# REPROVISION_TC_CLIENT_ID=project/releng/quarantine-worker
# REPROVISION_TC_ACCESS_TOKEN=...
